parameters:
Mage Relm: Even though we have permission to come to the
sunken city, we must do something about this unidentified
substance...
Thief Nora: It's okay because Relm-san is a genius!

Priestess Sophia: That's right, because I'm the next
Archmage.

Clea: We can only rely on Relm-san, so please do your best
to fulfill the request.

Mage Relm: Hehe, if you're going to say that much, I have
no choice! I don't know if you're a hero or what, but I'll
show you my magic!

Mage Relm: Huff...huff... I won't be scared, not even a
bit.
Thief Nora: U-Um, maybe we should give up already...

Mage Relm: We've come this far, we can't back down! There's
definitely a secret to this magic circle!

Mage Relm: Please watch! This moment where this great
genius surpasses the ancient spell formula--

Bard: Ahaha, no matter how many times I try, it's
impossible.

Bard: Your magic borrows the power of demons, but my magic
borrows the power of the gods, so it's a completely
different thing.

Bard: I can investigate this place starting now, but I
can't keep unlocking the seal forever.
Bard: Let me know when you're ready to go inside.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Bard: Are you ready to go inside? Once you enter, you won't
be able to come out right away, but is that okay?

Bard: I think it's a good decision. Once the seal is
lifted, it will become a place that is not connected to
reality.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Bard: Can you step away from the magic circle for a
moment?

Bard: Oh, small sun of Sol... I shall lift the seal of the
foolish city that has been judged.

Clea: Speaking of a test of skill, a bard... no, that's not
it.

Clea: Is it about being able to fight against a legendary
hero?

Mage Relm: It's impossible to win... because magic is an
entirely different power.

Priestess Sophia: You could say that I am a mediator of
the world, but it's impossible for me to do it sober... even
if I'm drunk, I'll still try to correct it.

Thief Nora: I can't even imagine being able to win, let
alone confront them.
Clea: I still want to challenge it.

Clea: Looking back now, I have fought against various
strong opponents during our long journey.

Clea: There were mostly opponents I couldn't respect or
understand, but I believe we have grown through challenging
battles.

Clea: There is no chance of winning against them, that's
for sure. However, I believe it will make us grow.
Priestess Sophia: Nora-chan, Relm-chan, let's give up.

Priestess Sophia: Once Clea-chan has become like this, she
can't be stopped.
Thief Nora: Surely, our lives won't be taken, right!?

Mage Relm: If Clea-san has decided, I will follow. However,
if we're going to fight, let's go with the intention to
win.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Mage Relm: This is the remains of judgment... the place
where the old Magic Academy used to be.

Thief Nora: Is this glass...? It feels strange... I have a
really unpleasant feeling about this place.

Mage Relm: Even I don't understand. I've never seen a
substance like this before.

Bard: You've come after all. I always thought you were
someone who would never give up.

Clea: Who exactly are you? If the story of the Archmage is
true... you haven't aged.

Bard: There are various names and it's complicated, but I
guess the easiest one to understand would be 'Hero', right?

Bard: You could say that we were left to clean up after the
Three Goddesses, right? It's really terrible how we just
disappear so quickly.

Priestess Sophia: The symbol of the Three Goddesses'
blessing... Wasn't that just a myth...!?

Mage Relm: Ah, it doesn't matter who you are! Please tell
me why you're getting in my way!

Bard: The grimoire you're trying to create holds the
potential to become their exit.

Bard: The demons sealed in the grimoire will come out
through the 'Blank Grimoire' you create.

Bard: If something like that were to happen, it's certain
that the demons would wreak havoc in this world.
Clea: Ah, a grimoire from which demons will come out...

Bard: I killed 7 of them, so the remaining 65 will come
out. The threat of the demons is nothing compared to that of
dragons.

Bard: That's why I'm stopping you, isn't it simple? I don't
mind killing demons, but you all will lose your magic.

Mage Relm: Ah, that's just a possibility, right!? I won't
give up on my dreams based solely on your speculation.

Mage Relm: W-What is it? Are you all really believing what
this person is saying!?

Mage Relm: First of all, what evidence is there that this
person is a hero--

Priestess Sophia: We were able to move from Myukos to
Kanonas in an instant...

Priestess Sophia: Doesn't Relm-chan understand better than
anyone else that this person is not normal?

Thief Nora: Ah, um, I, well, I'm against it because if
demons come out, important people might die.

Mage Relm: C-Clea-san, you're different, right!? You've
made the impossible possible, you'll support me, won't
you!?
Clea: I will stay with Relm-san until she is convinced.
Mage Relm: That's right! As expected of Clea-san!

Clea: I will stay with Relm-san until she is convinced. I
want Relm-san to not give up on her dreams.

Mage Relm: W-Why...even though we promised to fulfill our
dreams together...!

Mage Relm: If you interfere with our dreams... even my
friends won't show mercy...

Mage Relm: I will show you a miraculous moment and prove
that everything that person is saying is a lie!

Mage Relm: Haa... haa... I-I haven't given up yet! I
absolutely, absolutely won't give up...!

Mage Relm: Come on, please! No matter how many times, no
matter how many times, I will stand up!
Priestess Sophia: Clea-chan... this is enough!

Thief Nora: Y-Yes, that's right! Let's stop fighting among
ourselves, okay?

Mage Relm: W-What's wrong! It's not like I mind having a
one-on-one battle--
Clea: I will stay with Relm-san until she is convinced.
Clea: So please don't make that face.

Mage Relm: I-I... because... it's been my dream since I was
little... something like that...

Clea: Once, I was scared and tried to run away. But I was
able to pick up the sword again because everyone was there
for me.

Clea: That's why I'll stay by your side, Relm-san, until
you're convinced.

Mage Relm: Huff... I-I understand, you know? That this
person is the hero, and I absolutely can't defeat them.

Mage Relm: Ugh, but giving up like this, it's... even
though we've come this far all of a sudden, to be told it's
no good, ugh...

Mage Relm: I didn't know that my dream could be in
danger... If I had known, I would have chosen a different
dream... Ugh, ahhhhh!
Clea: Because we're together... it'll be alright.

Bard (I thought she was someone who would never give up no
matter what).

Bard (Come to think of it, while I've buried many
individuals, I haven't buried many who were surrounded by
companions.)
Bard (I see, so that's how it is)

Mage Relm: There's no way I'm alright! I have a lot of
regrets about not being able to complete the grimoire.
Mage Relm: That's why I'll stay with you all day today.

Mage Relm: Wait a moment! You're coming too, I'll sing you
a terrible song!

Mage Relm: Alright, let's go to Clea's house. Today, I'll
tell you all about myself, so listen carefully!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Kanonas Region / Sunken City\c[0]

Mage Relm: Haa...haa... Just a little more and my dream
will come true... Right here... my dream!

Mage Relm: Please move aside! I'm going to make the miracle
that no one else could achieve, my dream!

Bard: You really are someone who never gives up on their
dreams. You're definitely someone who can't be easily
discouraged.
Bard: Then there's only one thing to do.

Bard: Oh, small sun of Sol... I shall pass judgment upon
the fools in your name.
